# The mantle is the layer of the Earth between the crust and the outer core


## The mantle is mostly solid
- It undergoes plastic deformation

### Factors in magma production
- To melt:
	- Increase temperature
	- Decrease pressure
	- Add water
- To crystallize:
	- Cool liquid
	- Increase pressure
	- Remove water

## Hot spots and mantle plumes
![Pasted image 20220906135215.png|200](data:image/png;base64,)
- Hot spots do not move, but crust moves on top of it, creating belts of volcanic activity
- Yellowstone is a hotspot, and there is a belt of dead volcanoes at areas it used to be
